pr_review_comment_body:
You can't say whether something is better or worse based on amount_abs. You should use the is_regression property.
Also, you could probably express this more concisely by aggregating the alerts into improvement / regression categories, then doing a map/join on the groups.

E.g. (omitting some details):
```js
var resultStr = "";
var improved = _.filter(alertSummary.alerts, function(alert) { return !alert.is_regression && alert.visible; });
var regressed = _.filter(alertSummary.alerts, function(alert) { return alert.is_regression && alert.visible; });
if (improved.length > 0) {
   resultStr += "Summary of tests that improved:\n" + _.map(improved, function(alert) { return alert.title + '-' + ... }).join('\n') + "\n";
}
...
return resultStr;
```

This could be a new classmethod:

```py
@classmethod
def FromRSAKeyPath(cls, path):
  ...
  return cls(pub, priv)
```

If you provided just a name, you would have to run this three times to know the three parameters you were missing. I would recommend something like:
```Python
missing = []
if not resource_group_name: missing.append('--resource-group/-n')
if not resource_type: missing.append('--resource-type')
...
if missing:
  raise CLIError('Missing the following: {}. Alternatively, use --id'.format(' '.join(missing)))
```

Alternatively, simply reuse the usage statement from the old code, as that makes clear what is required as well as the alternative.

I believe (not sure) that you can stack these

```python
@convert.register(...)
@convert.register(...)
def ...
```

This is super minor - I was suggesting something like this:
```python
if isinstance(data_type, ModelPropertyType):
    return data_type
return ModelPropertyType(data_type=data_type)
```

I'd get rid of the `device_os` tbh. I don't see much value in doing this check. What we could do instead is replace the `device_os` with a `fail_on_miss` bool that does something like:

```
try:
    return reverse_mapping[long_int] + str(interface_number)
except KeyError:
    if fail_on_miss:
          raise
    return long_int+str(interface_number)
```
